1.2 Hazards include: 
 ‚Ä¢ Inhalation of asbestos fibers could lead to a debilitating lung disease and certain 
forms of lung cancer; 
‚Ä¢ The effect of asbestos exposure is cumulative i.e. the more exposure the higher the 
risk and consequence; 
‚Ä¢ Exposure to larger RCF material is associated with eye, skin and upper respiratory 
tract irritation; 
‚Ä¢ Inhalation of smaller very fine fibers has been linked to cancer.  
 
