3.3  Segregation 
‚Ä¢ Waste material shall be segregated at the source. This is to ensure the correct 
disposal for the waste stream; 
‚Ä¢ Hazardous waste not to be mixed with non-hazardous waste. There shall be a 
dedicated labelled bin for all types of identified waste; 
‚Ä¢ Recyclable waste (paper, wood, scrap metal, plastic etc) to be segregated from non- 
recyclable waste; 
‚Ä¢ Segregated recyclable waste from BGC locations shall not be mixed up with non-
recyclable waste. 
3.4  Storage 
Waste containers (skip, drums) shall: 
‚Ä¢ Be labelled with correct information to clearly communicate the content; 
‚Ä¢ Be compatible with contents (refer to MSDS sheet for restrictions on container types 
and chemicals); 
‚Ä¢ Be in good condition;  
‚Ä¢ Be sealable where hazardous wastes are to be contained and be resistant to 
