1 Overview and Hazards  
1.1 Housekeeping is a practical method of creating a safer workplace and reducing 
incidents by keeping the work area free of obstruction and waste. Good 
housekeeping reflects the level of professionalism and standards of its staff and it 
prevents accidents at work. 
Good housekeeping practices begin in the office and this behaviour shall extend to 
the way worksites are managed. This WMP establishes the minimum requirements 
and provides safe working practices for housekeeping. 
