#18 HSE Event Reporting, Investigation and Learning 
 
1 Overview and Hazards 
1.1 The purpose of this WMP is to ensure the correct action is taken after the occurrence of 
an HSE Event. An HSE Event is an unplanned event or chain of events that has, or could 
have, resulted in injury or illness, damage to our assets, the environment or an impact to 
our communities. 
All HSE Events including HSE incidents, Near Misses and Observations (incl unsafe 
act/conditions RAM3+) related to our activities shall be reported and investigated so that 
further risk can be mitigated, actions can be taken to prevent recurrence and to enable 
compliance with regulatory requirements and BGC standards. 
