out system is to minimize the risk to people, the environment and assets from exposure 
to energy (pressure, electrical, kinetic, temperature, etc) and hazardous substances 
during invasive maintenance, through effective isolation of equipment and the 
placement of locks and tags. For all types of isolations (e.g., electrical and mechanical / 
piping) systems / equipment being isolated must be tested to verify zero energy (test to 
