Work Management Procedure 
#26 Personal Protective Equipment (PPE) 
  
1 Overview and Hazards 
1.1 PPE is equipment worn to reduce severity of injuries resulting from exposure to hazards 
in the workplace. 
1.2 Hazards 
Hazards in the workplace include among others chemical, radiological, physical, 
electrical, mechanical hazards as per WMP #13 Hazard identification. PPE is the least 
effective control in the Hierarchy of Controls   after hazard elimination, substitution, 
engineering and administrative controls.  
Hence PPE alone should not be relied upon to mitigate risk. 
